 \tan\alpha=\frac yx=\frac43, 
 \sin\alpha=\frac y{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}=\frac 4{\sqrt{3^2+4^2}}=\frac45 
 \cot\alpha=\frac xy=\frac1{\tan\alpha}=\frac1{\frac43}=\frac34. 
